# Phase 03 / Cycle 4 — Writer RED — Stale `/building/authentication.mdx` reproduction

Reproduction surface: read the current page at the frozen SHA, then confirm the
factual claims fail against `~/code/fraiseql@d0a4ed4ec1770c70707f68fd9019f2b561d87461`.

Date: 2026-05-30
SHA:  d0a4ed4ec1770c70707f68fd9019f2b561d87461
Page: `src/content/docs/building/authentication.mdx` @ HEAD `1277c29`

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Observation 1 — Page L8 "Python SDK is compile-time only" framing is correct as
architecture but the page treats `@fraiseql.field(requires_scope=...)`,
`@fraiseql.type(requires_role=...)`, and `inject={"jwt:sub"}` as the *primary*
authentication surface. These are field-level access-control hooks that ride on
TOP of an already-validated JWT — they do nothing without a configured
authenticator. The page never explains how to configure the authenticator.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The actual authentication surface at the frozen SHA — what the page MUST cover:

  1. `[auth]` TOML section (OIDC).  Source-of-truth shape:
       crates/fraiseql-core/src/security/oidc/providers.rs:L48-L143
     deserialised by the server directly from `ServerConfig::auth`:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/mod.rs:L293-L307
     wired into the OIDC validator at startup:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/builder.rs:L308-L319

  2. `[auth_hs256]` TOML section (HS256 testing mode, #217 / v2.1.6).  Shape:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/hs256.rs:L24-L39
     wired into the auth middleware at startup via `build_hs256_auth`:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/builder.rs:L19-L39
     Mutually exclusive with `[auth]`.

  3. `[auth.me]` sub-section (`GET /auth/me` endpoint, v2.1.5 / issue #193).
     Shape:
       crates/fraiseql-core/src/security/oidc/providers.rs:L13-L41
     Mount logic:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/routing/auth.rs:L81-L101
     Handler:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/routes/auth.rs:L432-L460

  4. `[security.api_keys]` (compiled-schema only, NOT direct TOML).  Shape:
       crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/security.rs:L358-L399
     Wiring:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/api_key.rs:L237-L251
     Reads from `schema.security.additional["api_keys"]` — i.e. user puts the
     section in `fraiseql.toml`, then `fraiseql-cli compile` validates it and
     bakes it into `schema.compiled.json`, then the server reads it from there.

  5. `[security.token_revocation]` (compiled-schema only).  Shape:
       crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/security.rs:L463-L501
     Wiring:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/token_revocation.rs:L384-L437
     Same compiled-schema indirection as api_keys.
     Backends actually implemented at this SHA: memory, redis.
     CLI accepts `backend = "postgres"` (string) but server silently falls back
     to in-memory (token_revocation.rs:L425-L432 "Unknown revocation backend").

  6. `[security.pkce]` (compiled-schema only).  Shape:
       crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/security.rs:L309-L340
     PKCE store wiring:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/builder.rs:L114-L121
     Routes mounted only when (pkce_store, oidc_server_client) both present:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/routing/auth.rs:L25-L46
     S256 is the configured default (CodeChallengeMethod::S256 #[default]):
       crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/security.rs:L313-L316

  7. `[security.state_encryption]` (compiled-schema only).  Shape:
       crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/security.rs:L284-L306
     Wiring:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/builder.rs:L108-L113
     Key sourced from env var (key_source = "env", key_env = "STATE_ENCRYPTION_KEY"
     by default).

  8. `[security.rate_limiting]` (compiled-schema only).  Shape:
       crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/security.rs:L181-L249
     Server-side wiring:
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/initialization.rs:L186-L260
     Per-endpoint dispatch (auth_start / auth_callback / auth_refresh):
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/middleware/rate_limit/in_memory.rs:L59-L100
     **CAVEAT** — CLI accepts `failed_login_max_attempts` and
     `failed_login_lockout_secs`, but the server runtime config
     (`RateLimitingSecurityConfig` in `crates/fraiseql-server/src/middleware/
     rate_limit/config.rs:L7-L52`) does NOT have those fields. They are
     silently dropped on the server side. FW-15-class (CLI/runtime TOML schema
     split swallowed by missing `deny_unknown_fields` on `ServerConfig`).

  9. Nested JWT claims extraction (#246 / v2.3 era).  Source:
       crates/fraiseql-auth/src/jwt/mod.rs:L401-L490
       crates/fraiseql-core/src/security/auth_middleware/types.rs:L231-L320
     `Claims::email()` and `Claims::name()` normalise Azure AD
     `{"value": ...}` and OIDC `{"given": ..., "family": ...}` shapes.
     `jwt:email` / `jwt:name` / `jwt:display_name` are auto-available as RLS
     session-variable mappings:
       crates/fraiseql-core/src/security/security_context.rs:L120-L130

 10. JWT algorithm allowlist (S41 hardening).  Enforced at validation time:
       crates/fraiseql-core/src/security/oidc/token.rs:L363
     Default `allowed_algorithms = ["RS256"]`:
       crates/fraiseql-core/src/security/oidc/providers.rs:L152-L154
     A token presenting `alg: HS256` against an `["RS256"]` config is rejected
     before signature verification — the canonical algorithm-confusion defence.

 11. Cookie security on PKCE callback (when post_login_redirect_uri is set):
       crates/fraiseql-server/src/routes/auth.rs:L220-L246
     Cookie shape (L236):
       __Host-access_token="..."; Path=/; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict; Max-Age=…

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Observation 2 — STALE: page describes `OIDC_ISSUER_URL` env var as the OIDC
provider config.  This env var DOES NOT EXIST in the framework at the frozen
SHA.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  $ git -C ~/code/fraiseql grep -n OIDC_ISSUER_URL \
      d0a4ed4ec1770c70707f68fd9019f2b561d87461 -- 'crates/'
  (no matches)

Real OIDC config path: `[auth]` TOML section in `fraiseql.toml`, fields
`issuer` / `audience` / `additional_audiences` / `allowed_algorithms` / etc.
The Python-decorator framing (page L8-L12) mis-routes the reader: there is no
`OIDC_CLIENT_ID` / `OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET` / `OIDC_REDIRECT_URI` env-var triplet
in the framework either.  The real client-side fields live under
`[auth] discovery_url=`, `[auth] client_id=`, `[auth] client_secret_env=`,
`[auth] server_redirect_uri=` (per the PKCE builder warning at
`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/builder.rs:L362-L369`).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Observation 3 — STALE: page L194-L261 documents `[security.enterprise]`,
`[security.error_sanitization]`, `[security.rate_limiting]`, and
`[security.state_encryption]` blocks but ignores `[security.api_keys]`,
`[security.token_revocation]`, `[security.pkce]`, `[auth.me]`,
`[auth_hs256]`, and the entire `[auth]` block itself.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The page mentions HS256 NOWHERE.  HS256 testing-mode is the v2.1.6 #217
feature listed explicitly in the Cycle 4 spec; page has no awareness.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Observation 4 — STALE: page L200-L209 `[security.enterprise]` block has fields
`include_sensitive_data`, `log_level`, `async_logging`, `buffer_size`,
`flush_interval_secs` — these are not present in the CLI TOML schema's
`EnterpriseSecurityConfig` (`crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/
security.rs:L109-L154` — fields are `rate_limiting_enabled`,
`auth_endpoint_max_requests`, `auth_endpoint_window_seconds`,
`audit_logging_enabled`, `audit_log_backend`, `audit_retention_days`,
`error_sanitization`, `hide_implementation_details`,
`constant_time_comparison`, `pkce_enabled`).  The CLI uses
`deny_unknown_fields` on this struct so the page's fields cause `fraiseql-cli
compile` to fail loudly — but only AFTER the user gets past the rest of the
page.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Observation 5 — STALE: page L220-L246 `[security.rate_limiting]` block uses
`auth_start_max_requests`, `auth_start_window_secs`, `auth_callback_*`,
`auth_refresh_*`, `auth_logout_*`, `failed_login_max_requests`,
`failed_login_window_secs`.  Real CLI schema names:
`auth_start_max_requests` ✅, `auth_start_window_secs` ✅,
`auth_callback_max_requests` ✅, `auth_callback_window_secs` ✅,
`auth_refresh_max_requests` ✅, `auth_refresh_window_secs` ✅,
`auth_logout_max_requests` ✅, `auth_logout_window_secs` ✅,
**`failed_login_max_attempts`** (NOT `_max_requests`),
**`failed_login_lockout_secs`** (NOT `_window_secs`).
The page's `failed_login_*` fields fail CLI validation due to
`deny_unknown_fields` on `RateLimitingSecurityConfig`.

AND — even when the CLI accepts the correct names, the SERVER runtime config
(`crates/fraiseql-server/src/middleware/rate_limit/config.rs:L7-L52`) has NO
`failed_login_*` fields at all.  Brute-force protection via this TOML section
is a documentation-side promise the binary does not honour.  Same FW-15 class
as the observers TOML split.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

