────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Conclusion — RED reproduced.  The page is dangerous: it conflates field-level
access control with authentication itself, fabricates env-var-only OIDC
configuration that doesn't exist, mis-spells the brute-force protection
fields, and silently omits the entire `[auth]` / `[auth_hs256]` /
`[security.api_keys]` / `[security.token_revocation]` / `[security.pkce]` /
`[auth.me]` surface.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
